Citations
Date: 0/10/1985
Source: More Magazine
Author:
Vol / Page: 71
Edition:
Quote: But the buzz word in goat farming is `cashgora'. This stuff, hailed as the first new natural fibre to hit the world for 35 years, is an intermediate grade of fibre culled from crossbred goats. Judging what's what is a matter of microns - the measurement used to rate the fineness of the fibre diameter. ... Cashmere is the finest ... at no more than 19.5 microns. Cashgora goes up to 25 microns. Mohair measures anywhere from 23 to 40 microns.
